value: Long sword of cinquedea type, in excavated condition. The acutely arched cross, cusped at the ecusson, survives, but the plates of ivory (?walrus ivory) which formed the hilt are considerably perished. The arched cap of steel which would have formed the pommel is missing. Inlaid in the ivory grip are three small roundels of filigree work in latten.

description: sword, cast, decorated with plate and inlaid ivory

summary_title: The Sword in the Age of Chivalry
notes: Cf. The Oakeshott sword, plate 44A and B, p. 78
